      "writtenOn": "2020-08-18T14:42:13Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Be careful not to remove 1.0 as a texture coordinate. The rasterizer wants to fill in the interval from u_0 to u_1. If u_1 starts out as 1 and ends up going to 0 then you\u0027ll end up texturing backwards, i.e., from u_0 down to 0 rather than from u_0 up to 1.",
